<br>
Even on normal blues, all my characters have mastered all languages.  I love the language thing and wish there was more reason to do it on all servers (eg. add language to faction, have local NPCs only speak native, etc. etc.).  I can assure you that 1 char per line, 5 lines, is the fastest way to raise up skill.<br>
<br>
On FV, with 1C/5L, you can often skill-up while in the zone transition state -- no waiting about for a skill-up before zoning, you get it as your first message.  This lets you just ping-pong back and forth getting skill-ups.  Still takes 100 zones per language, but at least there's no sitting about after zoning. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 195<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/3/02 2:09:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Server filter ..</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt; I can assure you that 1 char per line, 5 lines, is the fastest way to raise up skill.&gt;&gt;<br>
