<br>
I guess what I meant didn't fully get across.  If you're in a city whose members primarily speak a foreign language, and you're going to be there a while, it may be in your interest to sit in amongst a number of people who are just...  talking.  The front gates of Qeynos, for example, the front entrance to Felwithe, the bank in Kelethin, etc.  People talk all the time in those places, and if you're doing something else (burning up those 20 wolf meats making steaks, for example), you might as well sit in one of those high-traffic areas to do it.  You might, as a bonus, learn a bit of the foreign language just sitting there.<br>
<br>
